  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*: The main page of the DApp CryptoKitties (https://www.cryptokitties.co/) appears all messed up, with images torn by a black horizontal bar, text where it should not be and flickering images. This happens when the user scrolls the page up and down several times. Here are two screenshots of the appearance of the page:\r\n\r\nScreenshot 1\r\n![whatsapp image 2018-08-02 at 17 19 10](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/23058833/43593663-b0c1db54-9678-11e8-88e5-ee18810cd476.jpeg)\r\n\r\nScreenshot 2\r\n![whatsapp image 2018-08-02 at 17 18 52](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/23058833/43593665-b0dfee14-9678-11e8-8a8d-ea46a9d4c98d.jpeg)\r\n\r\nHere is a video reproducing the bug (bug is seen from 0:40):\r\nhttps://drive.google.com/file/d/1QgENdgAlotuilhrQxum8oBf1OCGRV20y/view?usp=sharing\r\n\r\nThis issue has been reproduced in an Android device. Not been able to check on iOS devices.\r\n\r\nThe issue was reproduced 6 times/6 attempts.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what you expected to happen.)\r\nThe expected behavior was that independently of the times the user scrolls the page, the display of its layout will always be the same.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what actually happened.)\r\nThe actual behavior is that the page presents elements where they shouldn't be, cut through with a black line or flickering.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\n\r\n1- Open Status\r\n2- Go to Home\r\n3- Tap on \"+\"\r\n4- Open DApp\r\n5- Select CryptoKitties\r\n6- Select Open\r\n7- Scroll down until the end of the page\r\n8- Scroll up until the top of the page\r\n9- Repeat steps 7 and 8, three times\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nStatus version: 0.9.24 (6291), PlayStore, 1 August 2018\r\nOperating System: Android\r\nDevice: Huawei ALE-L21 with Android 6.0\r\nScreen resolution: Huawei->720x1280 pixels\r\n\r\n<blockquote><img src=\"https://www.cryptokitties.co/images/share.png\" width=\"48\" align=\"right\"><div><img src=\"/icons/android-icon-192x192.png\" height=\"14\"> CryptoKitties</div><div><strong><a href=\"https://www.cryptokitties.co\">CryptoKitties | Collect and breed digital cats!</a></strong></div><div>Collect and trade CryptoKitties in one of the worldâ€™s first blockchain games. Breed your rarest cats to create the purrfect furry friend. The future is meow!</div></blockquote>\r\n<blockquote><img src=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/umsMp4lSlGQ6u-n6J__zK3wN_dN0_L3pWb_Nrrbl87VgoVx1Ew4RhpsKs3I=w1200-h630-p\" width=\"48\" align=\"right\"><div>Google Drive</div><div><strong><a href=\"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1QgENdgAlotuilhrQxum8oBf1OCGRV20y/view?usp=sharing&usp=embed_facebook\">CryptoKitties_mainpage_not_loading_correctly.mp4</a></strong></div></blockquote>",
